    "opacity-rest-classify-max": 0.42,
    "opacity-active-classify-min": 0.9,
    "_classify_note": "REVISION (perception-brief §9b/§10.1,4): engine.js classifies each dot's contributed premultiplied energy every frame by its OWN current alpha -- alpha <= opacity-rest-classify-max is rest-tier (dimmed by emphasis.rest-dim), alpha >= opacity-active-classify-min is active-tier (boosted by emphasis.active-boost). The 0.42-0.90 band (dead 0.55 / expiring 0.55, both already-audited receding states) is deliberately left unclassified so this fix does not disturb FIX #1 (S8)."
  },
  "emphasis": {
    "_note": "REVISION (perception-brief §2,§4,§7,§9b,§10): the resting-field-dim / active-subset-boost + onset-pulse behavior. Swatch-hex changes cannot buy the recommended 3:1 identity/side-vs-field.rest separation (field.rest's own luminance is already high enough that even white clears only ~2.1:1 against it) -- this is an alpha/energy-level fix in engine.js's FRAG_POINTS and VERT_POINTS, not a color-token fix, and it applies to every scene automatically because it keys off each dot's alpha, not its scene-assigned hue.",
    "rest-dim": 0.6,
    "active-boost": 1.15,
    "pulse-window": 0.25,
    "pulse-size-gain": 0.35,
    "pulse-luminance-gain": 0.5,
    "pulse-color-epsilon": 0.05,
    "_pulse_note": "pulse-window is a fraction of each dot's own post-stagger progress u in [0,1] (not a wall-clock duration), so the onset pulse is scrub-safe and automatically absent under prefers-reduced-motion (A===B there, so aColA==aColB and pulse-color-epsilon is never cleared)."
  },
